cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes an improved version of a recurrent variational autoencoder for text modeling. It also uses Wasserstein objective, which is a popular technique in machine learning. 

It can also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language modeling and text generation tasks. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new method for improving the performance of a machine learning model. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with generative models, which are also used in computer vision tasks such as image generation. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a new method for training neural networks.
